snippet.textDisplay:
The ONE thing that will ALWAYS break me down is we a STRONG grown man cry. It tears me up every single time. I am not a fan of basketball so I really didn't know too much aboutt Kobe, but when I heard about what happened to him, his daughter and the players and family on her team as well as the pilot....I decided to learn more about him. I watched a documentary that followed his years through his basketball career and I bawled like I knew him my whole life.

The growth I saw in him was so profound that you could not help but love him for who he became. He went from being and individualized player that was focused only on himself putting up all the points, to being a team player that worked so well with the other players, to becoming a phenomenal team leader that was one of the greatest I have ever seen. Not many will have have the insight or willingness to recognize the needs of their team or have the potential to show such extreme growth in the positive way that he did, but we all could learn a little something by it.

All I can say is... I get it now. I understand why he was loved and respected so much and by so many. To his FAMILY, FRIENDS, and FANS...I give my condolences. May they all R.I.P. up there in Heaven. I am sure they definitely celebrated up there when they welcomed one of the good ones back home again.
